# Database — Skills & Conventions

## Before writing

- Read `docs/db.md` (index + migration counter) and the `docs/db/*.md` of the touched area.
- Apply the cross-cutting code-quality skills → see `.claude/rules/code-quality.md` (`writing-plans` for complex migrations, `verification-before-completion` before applying).

## Core skill

**[SKILL_DB]** — schema design, complex queries, indexes, performance.

## Conventions

Follow conventions in CLAUDE.md § "Conventions (non-negotiable)" and area docs.

## Migration workflow

1. Create migration file in `[MIGRATIONS_DIR]`
2. Update DB area docs (`docs/db.md`, `docs/db/[table].md`)
3. Update `docs/planning.md` if applicable
4. Register in `docs/changelog.md`
5. Pre-commit: invoke `migration-checker` agent ALWAYS before committing .sql files

## After modifying, update

Update DB area doc in the same act.
